export default function About() { return ( <>

Hello! üëãüèº I'm Faisal Karim, a passionate and dedicated individual with a love for programming and technology. From my early days in year 7, programming has been more than just a hobby for me - it's a way of life. Currently pursuing a double degree in Robotics and Mechatronics Engineering (Hons) and Computer Science at Swinburne University of Technology, I am committed to pushing the boundaries of what technology can achieve.

Skills

I have a diverse skill set that includes proficiency in:

  • Kotlin
  • C#
  • Ruby
  • CSS, HTML, Javascript
  • Matlab
  • Java

My experience extends to various domains, including Android development, web development, and creating Windows applications using WinForms and WPF.NET. As a Web Crawling Analyst at Jora, I am actively engaged in dynamic field of web technologies.

Professional Experience

I bring real-world experience from my roles at Jora as Web Crawling Analyst, Telstra as a Sales Consultant, Hampton Park Secondary School as a Helpdesk Person, and my recent internship at Universal Biosensors. These experiences have enriched my problem-solving abilities and enhanced my understanding of the intersection between technology and user needs.

Academic Achievements

In year 11, I achieved a remarkable feat by scoring in the top 0.3% of the state for my software development skills. Currently maintaining a GPA of 3.950 at university, I am committed to academic excellence.

Leadership and Teamwork

My high school years were marked by active involvement in leadership positions, where I honed my skills in teamwork, communication, and project management. These experiences have shaped me into a well-rounded professional with the ability to thrive in collaborative environments.

Join me on this exciting journey where technology meets creativity, and let's create innovative solutions together!

); }
